<p>In reality, the Earth does not rotate at a constant speed throughout the year. Natural time, like UTC, uses an average of these variations to create a regular and practical temporal flow for daily use, while preserving the accuracy of actual observations for sunrise and sunset. It's a balance between pure astronomical precision and everyday practicality.</p>
